## `eyecalib.1`

```roff
.TH EYECALIB 1 "May 2026" "tobii4c" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
eyecalib \- fullscreen Tobii eye tracker calibration utility for X11

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B eyecalib

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B eyecalib
creates a fullscreen calibration environment for supported
Tobii Eye Tracker 4C devices under X11.

The utility generates a calibration mesh used for gaze correction,
adaptive edge compensation and realtime pointer mapping.

The generated calibration file is stored in:

.B ~/.local/tobii_4c/calx11.conf

The calibration file is later used by
.BR eyemouse (1)
for gaze correction and pointer control.

.SH FEATURES
.IP \[bu] 2
Fullscreen borderless calibration

.IP \[bu]
3x3 calibration mesh

.IP \[bu]
Barycentric mesh warp preparation

.IP \[bu]
Adaptive edge reachability

.IP \[bu]
Realtime gaze validation

.IP \[bu]
Dynamic screen resolution handling

.IP \[bu]
Retry and recalibration support

.IP \[bu]
Local per-user calibration storage

.IP \[bu]
Low latency tracking preparation

.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.local/tobii_4c/calx11.conf
Calibration mesh configuration.

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR eyemouse (1)

.SH AUTHOR
Uwe Niethammer
